# Alternate Depot for Memberships

It is now possible to assign an **alternate depot** to a membership, used only for deliveries matching a secondary delivery cycle.

This is useful, for example, when a depot is only served every other week. A member can keep their usual depot for the matching weeks and pick up their basket at another depot on the remaining weeks.

This new option is available at the bottom of the **Deliveries** section of the membership admin form. It includes:

- the alternate depot
- its specific price
- the delivery cycle on which it should apply

The alternate depot is also shown on the membership page, included in the memberships CSV export, and automatically kept when renewing a membership.

Find more information about this feature in [the deliveries handbook](/handbook/deliveries#alternate-depot).
